30 Day Kaizen Accelerator OS
Development Plan and Proposed GitHub Docs Layout
Product Positioning
Scope in days в†’ baseline in a week в†’ improve in a week в†’ prove results in a month.
Executive Summary
The 30 Day Kaizen Accelerator OS should be built as a web, mobile, browser-extension, and API-based operating system for continuous improvement. It must support consultants, internal CI teams, process owners, enterprise admins, and AI agents that can automate Kaizen work inside governed environments.
Product Vision
The system turns the Kaizen Accelerator lifecycle into software that can be run in three modes:
Human-led
AI-assisted
Agent-led
The platform should:
identify the right process to improve
baseline current-state performance with evidence
orchestrate the event lifecycle
generate deliverables
validate implementation
prove results
feed the next intake opportunity into the pipeline
Product Principles
Deterministic before generative
No baseline, no improvement claim
No implementation, no value
Agent actions must be governed and auditable
Privacy-first process capture
Before/after evidence is required for ROI
Capability Model by Phase
Scoping вЂ” candidate scoring, problem framing, scope boundaries, charter draft
Baselining вЂ” workflow capture, event ingestion, timing, handoff, and defect analysis
Goal Setting вЂ” target metric recommendation and feasibility review
Charter Finalization вЂ” approvals, risks, and stakeholder alignment
Scheduling and Coordination вЂ” participant management and event logistics
Kaizen Event вЂ” current state review, future state design, decisions, and action backlog
Deliverables вЂ” SOPs, process maps, action plans, and documentation pack
Validation вЂ” implementation verification and proof collection
Benefits and Results вЂ” remeasurement, before/after comparison, ROI engine
Next Intake вЂ” portfolio prioritization and continuous improvement pipeline
