Development Roadmap
Phase 0 вЂ” Architecture and Product Definition
Finalize domain model, event schema, lifecycle state machine, agent roles, integration assumptions, and reference architecture.
Phase 1 вЂ” MVP Foundation
Build intake, scoping, capture, event ingestion, baseline metrics, deterministic process derivation, and current-state dashboard.
Phase 2 вЂ” Kaizen Delivery Layer
Add future-state design, decision logs, action tracking, and deliverables generation.
Phase 3 вЂ” Validation and ROI
Add implementation verification, remeasurement, benefits calculation, and portfolio reporting.
Phase 4 вЂ” Agent Operating System
Add agent identity, task APIs, policy enforcement, dry-run mode, approval routing, and environment automation.
Phase 5 вЂ” Enterprise Hardening
Add security controls, tenancy, observability, retention, deployment options, and compliance-oriented tooling.
Recommended MVP Scope
Web application for consultants and process owners
Browser extension for process capture
Process candidate scoring and scoping workflow
Event ingestion and baseline metrics engine
Current-state evidence dashboard
Basic charter builder, decision log, and action tracker
Before/after metric comparison and simple ROI worksheet
Agent Operating Model
Key agents should include:
Intake Agent
Baselining Agent
Process Analyst Agent
Facilitator Agent
Implementation Agent
Validation Agent
ROI Agent
Continuous Intake Agent
Each agent must operate with:
scoped permissions
human approval thresholds
dry-run support where appropriate
evidence-linked outputs
full audit logging
